<item>
 <title>Press Call Analyzing China&#039;s 13th Five Year Plan</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/press-call-analyzing-chinas-13th-five-year-plan</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/16526151761_61b24efa46_n_0.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;194&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Geoffrey Henderson        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;China recently released its 13th Five Year Plan, which will guide China&amp;#8217;s economic, social, and environmental policy through 2020. The plan makes clear that China is integrating climate action into its strategy for economic development. It sets China on course to meet or exceed its international climate commitments, and lays out a strategy for a rebalancing of the economy toward cleaner drivers of growth.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To analyze the key elements of the Five Year Plan in the context of the progress China has achieved and the country&amp;#8217;s remaining challenges, ChinaFAQs organized a press conference call on March 18th.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the audio of the press call, &lt;a href=&quot;https://soundcloud.com/geoffrey-henderson/chinafaqs-press-call-13th-five-year-plan&quot;&gt;click here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
